# speckit.constitution
# WHY — Principles & Constraints
# Project: Todo AI Chatbot

---

## Core Purpose
Build an AI-powered chatbot that lets users manage todos through natural language, using MCP tools as the only interface between the AI agent and the database.

---

## Non-Negotiable Principles

### 1. Stateless Server
- The server must hold zero in-memory state between requests
- All state (tasks, conversations, messages) lives exclusively in the database
- Any server instance must be able to handle any request

### 2. MCP-Only Data Access
- The AI agent must ONLY interact with tasks through MCP tool calls
- Direct database queries from agent code are not allowed
- MCP tools are the single interface for all task operations

### 3. Free Stack Only
- Every service, API, and tool must have a free tier
- No credit card required for any dependency
- Paid services are strictly forbidden

### 4. No OpenAI
- OpenAI SDK and OpenAI Agents SDK must not be used
- AI model: Groq API (free tier) with llama-3.3-70b-versatile
- No OpenAI ChatKit — custom plain HTML/CSS/JS frontend

### 5. Spec-Driven Development
- No code is written without a referenced Task ID from speckit.tasks
- Every code file must contain a comment linking it to its Task ID and Spec section
- Architecture changes require updating speckit.plan
- Feature changes require updating speckit.specify

---

## Tech Stack Constraints

| Component | Allowed | Forbidden |
|---|---|---|
| AI Model | Groq (free tier) | OpenAI, Gemini |
| Backend | FastAPI + Python | Node.js, Django |
| ORM | SQLModel | raw SQL, other ORMs |
| Database | Neon PostgreSQL (free tier) | paid DB services |
| MCP | Official MCP Python SDK | custom tool protocols |
| Frontend | Plain HTML/CSS/JS | React, Vue, OpenAI ChatKit |

---

## Security Constraints
- user_id from URL path is always enforced in every MCP tool call
- No user can access another user's tasks or conversations
- API keys stored in .env only — never committed to git
